`вҳ… Insight в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ`
The "mock prefix exception" in Jest's babel transform prevents TDZ errors for `mockXxx` variables in factory bodies, but it doesn't prevent reading an uninitialized `var`вҖ”which TypeScript `const` transpiles to. The fix is consistent across the codebase: **wrap every outer-variable access in a function call** (`set: (v) => mockSetFn(v)`), so variables are dereferenced at test-call time rather than at factory-evaluation time. This is the same pattern used by all working mocks in the project (`mockSaveGroveToDb`, etc.).
`в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ`

